  "prompt": "What are some good romantic movies with unusual ideas?",
  "response": "Okay, you're looking for romance movies with a twist! Here are some recommendations, categorized by the type of unusual idea they play with:\n\n**Time/Space Bending:**\n\n*   **About Time (2013):** A man learns he can travel in time and uses this ability to improve his romantic life, leading to heartwarming and thought-provoking exploration of relationships and choices.\n*   **The Lake House (2006):** Two people living in the same lake house, but two years apart, communicate through letters and fall in love, despite the temporal disconnect.\n*   **Safety Not Guaranteed (2012):** A cynical magazine intern investigates a man who placed a classified ad seeking a partner for time travel. A very quirky, sweet, and surprisingly grounded story.\n\n**Identity/Reality Bending:**\n\n*   **Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind (2004):** A couple undergoes a procedure to erase each other from their memories, but as their memories fade, they rediscover their love and fight to keep it. A visually stunning and emotionally powerful exploration of heartbreak and the importance of memory.\n*   **Her (2013):** A lonely writer develops a relationship with an AI operating system named Samantha, voiced by Scarlett Johansson. It's a poignant and thought-provoking look at connection in the digital age.\n*   **Ruby Sparks (2012):** A novelist writes a character into existence, and she comes to life. He then has to deal with the consequences of controlling someone he loves.\n\n**Supernatural/Magical Elements:**\n\n*   **Like Water for Chocolate (1992):** A woman in turn-of-the-century Mexico expresses her emotions through her cooking, with magically potent results that affect those who eat her food. Highly sensual and fantastical.\n*   **Stardust (2007):** A young man ventures into a magical realm to retrieve a fallen star for the woman he loves, encountering witches, pirates, and true love along the way. A charming and adventurous fantasy romance.\n*   **Cold Souls (2009):** This is a bit darker and more cerebral, but a man, overwhelmed by the pressures of acting, pays to have his soul removed. The soul is then stolen, and his life becomes increasingly bizarre and connected to a Russian mule.\n\n**Philosophical/Existential Romance:**\n\n*   **I Heart Huckabees (2004):** While primarily a quirky comedy, it involves a man seeking meaning in his life and forming connections with existential detectives who help him understand his relationship with the world. It's not a traditional romance, but love and connection are essential themes.\n*   **Wristcutters: A Love Story (2006):** A man kills himself after a breakup and ends up in a purgatory for suicides, where he searches for his ex-girlfriend. Darkly humorous and unexpectedly sweet.\n\n**Unusual Premise/Relationship Dynamics:**\n\n*   **Harold and Maude (1971):** A young man obsessed with death falls in love with a free-spirited, elderly woman. A cult classic with a very unique perspective on life and love.\n*   **Am\u00e9lie (2001):** While charming and whimsical, Am\u00e9lie's approach to romance is indirect and unusual, focusing on improving the lives of others before finding her own happiness.\n*   **Lars and the Real Girl (2007):** A socially awkward man develops a romantic relationship with a life-sized doll. While it seems absurd, the film is incredibly heartwarming and explores themes of loneliness, acceptance, and community.\n\n**Things to Consider When Choosing:**\n\n*   **Your Tolerance for Quirky/Weird:** Some of these are genuinely strange and may not appeal to everyone.\n*   **Genre Preference:** Do you prefer fantasy, sci-fi, drama, or comedy?\n*   **Emotional Tone:** Some are lighthearted, while others are more melancholic or thought-provoking.\n\nHopefully, this gives you some interesting options to explore!  Happy watching!\n",
